{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01873nFBSz8e4LW8cN846TGK","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\n     2→PROJECT: PrizmClaw\n     3→LANG: nodejs\n     4→MODULE_INDEX:\n     5→- src/bot: bot.prizm\n     6→- src/http: http.prizm\n     7→- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n     8→- src/routes: routes.prizm\n     9→- src/security: security.prizm\n    10→- src/services: services.prizm\n    11→- src/utils: utils.prizm\n    12→- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\n    13→RULES:\n    14→- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n    15→- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n    16→- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n    17→- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n    18→- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n    19→- MUST use messageRouter.processMessage() for all chat messages (Web + Telegram) — do not call executeAiCli directly for chat\n    20→- MUST call sessionBind.ensureReady() before any sync method in async route handlers\n    21→\n    22→UPDATED: 2026-03-22\n    23→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"98a56f18-1881-47f2-b30f-8934e38e981a","uuid":"dd382d08-7cb9-48d2-9a5a-ceba5393b672","timestamp":"2026-03-22T16:14:20.410Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/root.prizm","content":"PRIZM_VERSION: 1.0\nPROJECT: PrizmClaw\nLANG: nodejs\nMODULE_INDEX:\n- src/bot: bot.prizm\n- src/http: http.prizm\n- src/pipeline-infra: pipeline-infra.prizm\n- src/routes: routes.prizm\n- src/security: security.prizm\n- src/services: services.prizm\n- src/utils: utils.prizm\n- src/adapters: adapters.prizm\nRULES:\n- All HTTP routes use src/routes/api-routes.js as entry point\n- Telegram bot uses Telegraf framework with command handlers in src/bot/commands/\n- Services are registered in src/services/index.js\n- Security checks use security/ guards before command execution\n- Config loaded from src/config.js with environment variable support\n- MUST use messageRouter.processMessage() for all chat messages (Web + Telegram) — do not call executeAiCli directly for chat\n- MUST call sessionBind.ensureReady() before any sync method in async route handlers\n\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n","numLines":23,"startLine":1,"totalLines":23}}}
